All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
Ammo
Representation of a Ammo that gets shot from a blaster.
Blaster
Represents a blaster which shoots out ammo
Camera
This class represents the camera on the screen that you can use to move/look around
Coin
Representation of a coin that can be found in the maze
DrawingSurface
DrawingSurface is a surface where the game is performed and drawn.
Entity
Representation of entities that can be found throughout the maze
FixedWall
A FixedWall is a Wall that is fixed, thus players and entities cannot go through.
GameEndScreen
Represents the screen that is shown when the game ends.
GameScreen
Represents the screen of the game.
Interactable
Representation of an interactable box that can be found in the maze
Main
Main is the class where the program is executed.
Maze
A Maze represents a three dimensional maze of given dimensions.
Menu
Representation of a menu which gives the user important information about the game such as the story line and the controls
Monster
Representation of a monster that can be found in the maze
Pillar
A Pillar is a wall that connects two fixed walls.
Player
This class represents the player, a type of camera that moves along the maze, collides with Walls.
Screen
Representation of the different screens in the program
StartMenu
Representation of a start menu which is the first screen the user is presented with and allows them to start the game
Store
Representation of a store which gives and allow the user to buy upgrades for the game
Sword
Represents a sword which is a hand held weapon
UpgradeInfo
Representation of a upgrade info screen which gives the user information about all the upgrades they could buy and play with
Wall
Representation of walls that is the building components of the maze
Weapon
Represents a weapon which can be used by the user in the maze
